10/02/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The ruling coalition says it will work to gain a second mandate next year by updating its government programme.
Leaders of the coalition members -- the Movement for Rights and Liberties, the Bulgarian Socialist Party, and the National Movement for Stability and Progress -- met on Saturday (February 9th) in Hisar.
The session was also attended by ministers, deputy ministers and parliamentary group leaders.
(BNR, BNT, BGNES, Darik, BTV - 09/02/08)
